authorizations_search:
Table Name : authorizations_search
Description : This table contains information about all the transactions in sales and their details like status, date, network, payment methods etc. keywords Auth, Sale, Flow, Transaction
This table has the following columns : 
a_approvalCode (STRING) : Identifies if the authorization was approved or declined.. It contains values : "Declined", "Approved".
a_type (STRING) : Transaction type code e.g., sale, refund etc.. It contains values : "Pre Auth Request", "Purchase", "Return".
a_transactionDateTime (DATETIME) : Date & time of the authorization transaction.
a_accountNumber (STRING) : Card number used for authorization transaction.
a_cardExpiryDate (STRING) : Indicates expiration date on card.
a_amount (FLOAT64) : Amount requested for the authorization transaction.
a_currency (STRING) : Currency code used for the transaction.. It contains values : "USD".
a_network (STRING) : Name of the authorizing network associated with the transaction.. It contains values : "Mastercard", "Visa", "Star", "Pulse", "NYCE", "Discover", "American Express", "Unknown".
a_paymentMethod (STRING) : Identifies the method of payment used on the transaction.. It contains values : "Manual", "Mobile & ECommerce", "Credential on File".
a_declineReason (STRING) : Identifies the decline reason for the transaction.
a_authCode (STRING) : Authorization code from association(s). Generally, 6/7 alphanumeric code that gets printed on the receipt.
a_siteID (STRING) : An unique identifier assigned to the merchant. Also known as a MID.. It contains values : "311200311885".
a_processor (STRING) : Identifies the originating platform (Switch).. It contains values : "North".
a_merchantCategory (STRING) : Identifies the standard merchant category code assigned to the transaction.. It contains values : "5818".
a_customerName (STRING) : Name on the Card.. It contains values : "".
a_giftCardNumber (STRING) : Gift card number used for authorization transaction.. It contains values : "".
a_partnerOrderID (STRING) : Order identifier originated from Merchant.. It contains values : "".
a_source (STRING) : Indicates the source.. It contains values : "Regular".
a_sendMode (STRING) : Indicates store and forward mode of the transaction.. It contains values : "Normal".
a_mobileWallet (STRING) : Identifies wallet type indicator (e.g., Apple Pay, Samsung Pay, Google Pay, etc.).. It contains values : "Non Mobile Wallet".
a_ECIIndicator (STRING) : Indicates the electronic commerce indicator used for the transaction.. It contains values : "Channel Encrypted E-Comm", "Recurring Transaction", "No ECI Provided", "Secure E-Comm", "Non-Secure E-Comm".
a_terminalID (STRING) : Identifies terminal identifier for the transaction.. It contains values : "04221150".
a_CAVVResponse (STRING) : Identifies name verification result response from the authorizer.. It contains values : "Not Validated", "Not Validated - Erroneous Data", "Passed Validation", "Issuer Does Not Participate", "Failed Validation - Attempt".
a_AVSResponse (STRING) : Identifies the result, obtained from the cardholder's name, during address verification.. It contains values : "Not Provided", "Address & Zip Match", "Address & Zip Does Not Match", "Card Type Not Supported", "Information/System Not Available", "Retry", "Addr Only (Discover: Addr & Zip) Match", "Zip Matches, Address Does Not", "9 Digit Zip Matches, Address Does Not".
a_CVVResult (STRING) : Identifies the card verification value (CVV2) response from the authorizer.. It contains values : "Not Provided", "Match/Passed Validation", "No Match/Failed Validation", "Issuer Attempted/Not Complete".
a_banknetRef (STRING) : Indicates Mastercard assigned Banknet reference number.
a_subType (STRING) : Transaction sub type codes e.g., Pin, Signature, etc.. It contains values : "Not Provided".
a_cardGroup (STRING) : The group of the card that is used in the transaction.. It contains values : "Mastercard", "Visa", "Discover", "Amex", "Debit".
a_tokenId (STRING) : Token number.. It contains values : "".
a_tokenResponseInd (STRING) : Tokenization response indicator.. It contains values : "Success".
a_ordNo (STRING) : Order number sent by merchant.
a_nativeRejectCode (STRING) : The reject code as received from the front-end switches.
a_nativeDebitRejectCode (STRING) : Native debit reject code.. It contains values : "0S9", "062", "054", "014", "042", "051", "005", "012", "059".
a_linkResponseCode (STRING) : Identifies the Card N/w (i.e., VISA, Mastercard, Discover, AMEX) link response.
a_externalMid (STRING) : External merchant ID.. It contains values : "".
a_txnID (STRING) : Network transaction ID.
a_mrchTranId (STRING) : External reference ID.. It contains values : "".
a_DCCIND (STRING) : Identifies the acceptance of dynamic currency code transaction processing.. It contains values : "".
a_DCCCurrency (STRING) : Identifies non-local merchant enabled dynamic currency code.. It contains values : "N/A".
a_DCCAmount (STRING) : Identifies the total transaction amount in the currency of the card rather than in the currency of the place of purchase.. It contains values : ".00".
a_assocRespCode (STRING) : Identifies the initial association response code for the transaction.. It contains values : "Unknown", "Do Not Honor", "Expired Card", "Invalid Account", "Invalid Transaction", "Account Locked", "Lost or Stolen Card", "Invalid Merchant", "Do Not Retry", "Retry Later", "Retry the transaction with 3DS data", "Card has expired/Acnt was upgraded".
a_oldAccountNumber (STRING) : Old Card number.
a_nativeAuthOpAction (STRING) : Native Authorization Operation Action.. It contains values : "01", "2A", "2B", "2BE1", "2B06", "2BN1", "06", "011B", "011BN1".

chargebacks_search:
Table Name : chargebacks_search
Description : Chargebacks Search Table
This table has the following columns : 
cb_siteID (STRING) : Site ID (BE) - merchant number associated with each the business location.. It contains values : "311200311885", "372793590889".
cb_backendProcessor (STRING) : Internal settlement platform.. It contains values : "North".
cb_authNetwork (STRING) : Authorization network of the credit card utilized for the transaction.. It contains values : "Visa", "Debit/Other", "Discover", "Mastercard".
cb_receivedDate (DATETIME) : Date when the chargeback was initiated.
cb_statusDate (DATE) : Date for an expected response to the client.
cb_transactionDate (DATE) : Original date on a transaction that is being disputed and associated with a specific chargeback.
cb_adjDate (DATE) : Adjustment date.
cb_status (STRING) : Status of chargeback.. It contains values : "Closed", "Reversed".
cb_category (STRING) : Categorization of chargeback.. It contains values : "Debited", "Pre-Arbitration", "Reversed", "Auto Representment", "Merchant Accepted".
cb_workType (STRING) : Various stages of chargeback resolution.. It contains values : "First Chargeback", "Outgoing Pre-Arbitration", "First Chargeback Reversal", "Incoming Pre-Arbitration".
cb_winLoss (STRING) : Status of dispute, describing if it has been won, loss or pending.. It contains values : "Loss", "Win".
cb_Reason (STRING) : Descriptive reason associated with a specific chargeback.. It contains values : "Incorrect account", "Fraud (Card not present)", "Cancelled/Returned", "Fraud (Card present)", "Product/Service or Cash not received", "Cancelled recurring payment", "Fraud (No authorization)", "Cardholder dispute", "Credit not processed", "Point of error interaction error", "Duplicate processing", "Paid by other means", "Defective/Not as described", "Misrepresentation".
cb_ReasonKey (STRING) : Descriptive reason associated with a specific chargeback. (Code)
cb_adjustmentAmountSign (STRING) : Sign for adjustment amount that is being disputed.. It contains values : "+", "-".
cb_currency (STRING) : Currency code used for the transaction.. It contains values : "USD".
cb_chargebackAmount (FLOAT64) : Chargeback amount that is disputed by cardholder.
cb_dueDate (DATE) : A Chargeback due date is the deadline that you must respond by, in order to dispute a chargeback.
cb_transactionType (STRING) : Transaction type that identifies the transactions as a sale/refund etc.. It contains values : "Credit", "Sale".
cb_dispositionDate (STRING) : Disposition date.. It contains values : "07/16/2022", "08/01/2022", "07/21/2022".
cb_Disposition (STRING) : Describing final settlement of a chargeback.. It contains values : "Status Update to Closed", "Your case response has been rejected", "Case has been reversed", "Adjustment to Merchant", "Close Case", "Merchant Accepted Case".
cb_ECIndicator (STRING) : Electronic Commerce Indicator (ECI) is a value returned by Visa, MasterCard, JCB, and American Express etc. indicating the outcome of authentication attempted on transactions.. It contains values : "No ECI Provided", "Recurring Transaction", "Channel Encrypted E-Comm", "Secure E-Comm", "Single Payment Transaction (MOTO)".
cb_transactionAmount (FLOAT64) : Transaction amount that is being disputed.
cb_adjustmentAmount (FLOAT64) : Adjustment amount that is being disputed.
cb_accountNumber (STRING) : Card number used for the transaction.
cb_first6 (STRING) : First six digits of card number.
cb_last4 (STRING) : Last four digits of card number.
cb_invoiceNumber (STRING) : Invoice number associated with the inquiry.
cb_terminalId (STRING) : Terminal ID.. It contains values : "".
cb_disputeID (STRING) : Case number associated with a specific chargeback.
cb_referenceNumber (STRING) : Reference number associated with the inquiry.
cb_authCode (STRING) : Authorization code from association(s). Generally, 6/7 alphanumeric code that gets printed on the receipt.
cb_trackingNumber (STRING) : The tracking number of the disputed transaction.. It contains values : "".
cb_svcCd (STRING) : Identifies the transaction service code.. It contains values : "Unknown".
cb_merchantCategory (STRING) : Identifies the standard merchant category code assigned to the transaction.. It contains values : "Large Merchant Digital Goods (5818)", "Fast Food Restaurants (5814)".
cb_orderNumber (STRING) : Merchant order number.
cb_responseReceived (STRING) : Chargeback response received.. It contains values : "N", "Y".
cb_respondedDate (STRING) : Responded on date.
cb_externalMid (STRING) : External MID.. It contains values : "311200311885", "372793590889".
cb_paymentMethod (STRING) : Identifies the method of payment used on the transaction.. It contains values : "Unknown", "Mobile & ECommerce".
cb_sendMode (STRING) : Indicates store and forward mode of the transaction.. It contains values : "Normal".
cb_recurring (STRING) : Describes the recurrence type for the transaction.. It contains values : "Recurring", "One Time".
cb_mobileWallet (STRING) : Identifies wallet type indicator (e.g., Apple Pay, Samsung Pay, Google Pay etc.).. It contains values : "Non Mobile Wallet".
cb_tokenResponseInd (STRING) : Tokenization response indicator.. It contains values : "Success".
cb_captureMethod (STRING) : Capture method.. It contains values : "".
cb_preDisputeIndicator (STRING) : Pre dispute indicator.. It contains values : "N".
cb_paypalTransactionID (STRING) : Unique identifier for PayPal transaction.
cb_mobileIndicator (STRING) : Mobile indicator.. It contains values : "".
cb_receivedFromIssuer (STRING) : Received from issuer.. It contains values : "1".
cb_userData (STRING) : Discretionary data sent on transaction by the merchant.. It contains values : "".
cb_requestDate (STRING) : Request date.. It contains values : "07/16/2022", "08/01/2022", "07/21/2022".
cb_batchDate (DATE) : Date group of transactions was settled.
cb_batchNumber (STRING) : Number assigned to each group of settled transactions.. It contains values : "".
cb_airlineTicketNumber (STRING) : Airline industry only.. It contains values : "".
cb_submittedMerchantId (STRING) : Available for PSPs.. It contains values : "".
cb_softDescriptor (STRING) : Available for PFAC (Payment Facilitator Aggregator) only. Name of the Sub Merchant.. It contains values : "MSBILL.INFO".
cb_submittedTxnCurrencyCode (STRING) : ISO 4217 3 digit code representing the currency the transaction was processed in at the POS.. It contains values : "USD", "N/A".
cb_debitNetworkId (STRING) : Debit network description.. It contains values : "Unknown", "Star", "NYCE", "Pulse".
cb_customTracking (STRING) : nan. It contains values : "".
cb_origTranCurrency (STRING) : Transaction amount of the original presentment in transaction currency.. It contains values : "840".
cb_merchantSettleAmount (FLOAT64) : The amount settled with the merchant for the original presentment (that is, the amount posted to the merchant account), before the deduction of any charges.
cb_networkSettleCurrency (STRING) : Currency settled with the payment network for the presentment before the deduction of any charges.. It contains values : "".
cb_networkSettleAmount (STRING) : Amount settled with the payment network for the presentment (that is, the interchange settlement amount), before the deduction of any charges.. It contains values : "".
cb_origSlipNumber (STRING) : The OmniPay internal slip number of the original presentment.
cb_itemSlipNumber (STRING) : The OmniPay internal slip number of the transaction (that is, of the 1st chargeback, representment, and so on).. It contains values : "".
cb_memberMessageText (STRING) : Text supplied by the issuer with the incoming first or second chargeback, it can also be the text send with the REP. This is empty for items related to transfers.
cb_documentIndicator (STRING) : Indicates if a document was provided for the item type. This data is extracted from the original base II or IPM file and only populated for chargebacks items (1st and 2nd).. It contains values : "".
cb_retrievalRequestId (STRING) : Since this feed do not include RRQ this field is always empty.. It contains values : "".

cb_centralProcessingDate (STRING) : Central processing date of the latest incoming transaction for the chargeback case.. It contains values : "".
cb_partialAmountFlag (STRING) : Flag to indicate if the issuer has identified this chargeback as a partial chargeback.. It contains values : "".
cb_vmeAdditionalAuthMethod (STRING) : V.me additional auth method from the original presentment.. It contains values : "".
cb_vmeAdditionalAuthReasonCode (STRING) : V.me additional auth reason code from the original presentment.. It contains values : "".
cb_ppolProgramData (STRING) : PPOL program data from the original presentment.. It contains values : "".
cb_originalChargebackSlipNumber (STRING) : If the item type is a 1st or 2nd chargeback this field is equal to the field item_slip, but for presentment and transfer this field will indicate which is the related chargeback.. It contains values : "".
